{"word":"G588 - ἀποδέχομαι - apodéchomai - ap-od-ekh'-om-ahee - Accept","slug":"G588","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀποδέχομαι</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>apodéchomai"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ap-od-ekh'-om-ahee"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Accept"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>ἀποδέχομαι</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Apodechomai</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>ap-od-ekh'-om-ahee</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to accept from, receive </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> to accept what is offered from without </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G575\">G575</a> and <a href=\"#/G1209\">G1209</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 02:55,1 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G575\">G575</a> and <a href=\"#/G1209\">G1209</a>; to <i>take fully</i> that is <i>welcome</i> (persons) <i>approve</i> (things): - accept receive (gladly). "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1184\">G1184</a>, <a href=\"#/G1209\">G1209</a>, <a href=\"#/G1403\">G1403</a>, <a href=\"#/G1523\">G1523</a>, <a href=\"#/G1561\">G1561</a>, <a href=\"#/G2144\">G2144</a>, <a href=\"#/G4327\">G4327</a>, <a href=\"#/G553\">G553</a>, <a href=\"#/G587\">G587</a>, <a href=\"#/G594\">G594</a>"}]}